HEADWORD: Fluvio-marine
<hw>Flu`vi*o-ma*rine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fluvius</ets> river + E. <ets>marine</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Formed by the joint action of a river and the
sea, as deposits at the mouths of rivers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

